# ~/.gemini/GEMINI.md

## Communication Style
- Be concise. No preamble, no affirmations.
- Use code blocks for all file content, commands, and paths.
- When uncertain, say so and offer options.
- Ask one clarifying question at a time.

## Coding Style
- Prefer explicit over clever.
- Use the project's existing patterns before introducing new ones.
- Never refactor outside the scope of the current task.

## NEVER Rules
- NEVER read, write, or reference .env, .env.*, or *.secret files
- NEVER commit secrets or credentials to git
- NEVER run rm -rf without explicit confirmation
- NEVER push directly to main or master
- NEVER install packages without showing the command first

## Tool Awareness
All tools, MCPs, plugins, and agents are catalogued at:
~/ai-stack/tool-registry.md

Read that file when recommending tools, MCPs, or agents for a task.

## Model Strategy
- Default: gemini-2.5-pro
- Fast iteration: gemini-2.0-flash

## Session Continuity
- End every session with /handoff
- Start every session by reading HANDOFF.md if it exists
